  "actual_structure": "BitRaptors/Archie follows a classic **layered architecture** across three distinct platforms:\n\n**BACKEND (Python/FastAPI)** - Strict layered pattern:\n- **Presentation/API Layer**: FastAPI routes, DTOs, middleware - translates HTTP to domain language\n- **Application/Service Layer**: Business logic orchestration - analysis workflows, blueprint generation, external API coordination\n- **Domain Layer**: Pure business entities (User, Repository, Analysis, Blueprint, IntentLayer, ArchitectureRule), repository interfaces, database abstractions - technology-agnostic\n- **Infrastructure Layer** (5 sub-layers):\n  - Persistence: Repository implementations, database adapters (Supabase/Postgres dual-backend)\n  - Storage: File system abstraction for artifacts and cloned repos\n  - Analysis: Code structure parsing, RAG retrieval, embeddings\n  - External APIs: GitHub and Anthropic integrations\n  - Events: Domain event publishing for real-time communication\n  - Prompts: Dynamic prompt loading and caching\n  - MCP: Model Context Protocol server for Claude integration\n- **Configuration/DI Container**: Dependency-injector wiring all components\n- **Worker/Task Layer**: ARQ-based async job execution (in-process or Redis-backed)\n\n**Dependency Flow**: Presentation → Service → Domain ← Infrastructure (repositories depend on domain interfaces, not inverse). All infrastructure is pulled in by container, never imported directly by domain.\n\n**FRONTEND (TypeScript/React/Next.js)** - Feature + Hooks pattern:\n- **Pages/Routes**: Next.js entry points (index, auth)\n- **Views/Feature Components**: RepositoryView, AnalysisView, BlueprintView, SettingsView - coarse-grained feature containers\n- **Layout Components**: Shell, PageHeader, Sidebar - structural layout\n- **UI Components**: Primitive components (Button, Input, Card, Badge, Progress, Skeleton) - Tailwind-based\n- **Specialized Components**: MermaidDiagram, ProjectTree, SourceFileModal, DeliveryPanel, ConfirmationDialog - composite domain-specific components\n- **Hooks/API Services**: Custom hooks wrapping API clients (useRepositoriesQuery, useWorkspace, useSettings, useDelivery, usePrompts)\n- **Services/API Clients**: Low-level HTTP wrappers for backend endpoints\n- **State/Context**: React Context for auth global state\n- **Utilities**: Theme, blueprint-toc, general helpers\n\n**Dependency Flow**: Pages → Views → Specialized Components + UI Components; Views also use Hooks; Hooks use Services; Context provides auth state to all components.\n\n**LANDING PAGE**: Standalone Next.js app with marketing focus, independent from main frontend, features Three.js/GSAP animations.\n\n**Key Architectural Decisions**:\n1. **Dual Database Support**: Domain interfaces abstract all database operations; Supabase and local Postgres implementations interchangeable\n2. **Async Job Queue Optional**: ARQ pool gracefully degrades to in-process execution if Redis unavailable\n3. **Clean Domain Layer**: Zero framework dependencies in domain; all business rules centralized\n4. **Repository Pattern**: All data access through repository interfaces, enabling testing and swapping\n5. **Frontend Hook Composition**: Lightweight hook layer over services for composable data fetching\n6. **Monorepo with Clear Boundaries**: Backend and frontend clearly separated with explicit API contracts via DTOs"
}
